.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.CALENDARID" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.calendarId \- Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.calendarId
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]calendarId\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instances returns a string representing
the calendar used to interpret the internal ISO 8601 date.
.PP
See \f[CR]Intl.supportedValuesOf()\f[R] for a list of commonly supported
calendar types.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]calendarId\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
Use the \f[CR]withCalendar()\f[R] method to create a new
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] object with the desired new value.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using calendarId
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] date = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01\(dq);
console.log(date.calendarId); \f[I]// \(dqiso8601\(dq; default\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date2 = Temporal.PlainDate.from(\(dq2021\-07\-01[u\-ca=chinese]\(dq);
console.log(date2.calendarId); \f[I]// \(dqchinese\(dq\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] date3 = date2.withCalendar(\(dqhebrew\(dq);
console.log(date3.calendarId); \f[I]// \(dqhebrew\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R]
